               "text": "### Introduction\n\nWhen analyzing epic texts and poems, both recent and ancient, it is possible to observe the use of rhetorical figures (<htcite0>; <htcite1>), which are often not recognized and end up being interpreted literally.\n\nIn the study of the scientific method, we notice that at every stage, events and measurements are expected to yield literal results that can be reproduced (<htcite2>).\n\nAt first glance, these are completely different forms of writing, which leads us to an initial reflection:",
